The paper is focused on the field of Information Science and Retrieval, which is closely related to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The study involves a user study to construct a complex-valued vector space model of the user's cognitive state, which is a common approach in Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The use of Quantum Theory as a mathematical framework suggests a potential connection to the sub-category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC), which often involves the use of quantum algorithms. The study also involves the analysis of data, which suggests a potential connection to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Deep Learning (cs.DL).
